'''Jair Semedo Monteiro''' ({{IPA|pt|ʒɐ.ˈiɾ sɨ.ˈme.du mõ.ˈtej.ɾu|lang}}; born 29 December 1995), known as '''Yannick Semedo''' ({{IPA|pt|ja.ˈnik sɨ.ˈme.du|lang}}), is a Cape Verdean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Liga Portugal 2]] club [[S.C. Farense|Farense]] and the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

==Club career==
Semedo began his senior career in Cape Verde with GDR Celtic Praia in 2013. The following season, he moved to Portugal with GD São Roque in the Portuguese fifth division. His season there earned him a move to the [[C.S. Marítimo B|Marítimo reserves]] on 27 August 2015, where he stayed 3 seasons in the [[Campeonato de Portugal (league)|Campeonato de Portugal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dtudo1pouco.cv/rudy-monteiro-e-yannick-semedo-assinam-pelo-maritimo/|title=Rudy Monteiro e Yannick Semedo assinam pelo Marítimo &#124; DTudo1Pouco|date=27 August 2015}}</ref> He stayed in the CDP for 4 more seasons with [[C.F. União|União Madeira]], [[S.C. Beira-Mar|Beira-Mar]] and [[S.C. Salgueiros|Salgueiros]] respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://azscore.com/news/football/204722-football-yannick-semedo-formerly-of-vilaverdense-to-join-santa-clara|title=Football: Yannick Semedo (formerly of Vilaverdense) to join Santa Clara - azscore.com}}</ref> On 13 July 2022, he moved to [[Vilaverdense FC|Vilaverdense]] in the [[Liga 3 (Portugal)|Liga 3]], and in his debut season earned them promotion to the [[Liga Portugal 2]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.balai.cv/noticias/desporto/internacional-cabo-verdiano-yannick-semedo-troca-salgueiros-por-real-massama/|title=Internacional cabo-verdiano Yannick Semedo troca Salgueiros por Real Massamá|date=13 July 2022|website=Balai}}</ref> He extended his contract with the club on 7 July 2023 for 3 seasons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.balai.cv/noticias/desporto/futebol-internacional-cabo-verdiano-yannick-semedo-renova-com-lank-vilaverdense/|title=Futebol: Internacional cabo-verdiano Yannick Semedo renova com Lank Vilaverdense|date=7 July 2023|website=Balai}}</ref> On 29 December 2023, he terminated his contract with Vilaverdense after the club failed to pay his wages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.criolosports.com/index.php/en/criolos-no-estrangeiro/futebol-portugal-yannick-semedo-rescinde-contrato-com-o-lank-vilaverdense-por-incumprimento-salarial|title=Futebol Portugal: Yannick Semedo rescinde contrato com o Lank Vilaverdense por incumprimento salarial|date=8 October 2024|website=criolosports.com}}</ref>

On 3 January 2024, Semedo moved to [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]] on a 1.5 year contract, and helped them win the [[2023–24 Liga Portugal 2]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.acorianooriental.pt/noticia/santa-clara-anuncia-medio-yannick-semedo-como-reforco-por-uma-temporada-e-meia-356738|title=Santa Clara anuncia médio Yannick Semedo como reforço por uma temporada e meia - Açoriano Oriental}}</ref> On 2 July 2024, he joined [[F.C. Vizela|Vizela]] on a loan until 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.diariodominho.pt/noticias/desporto/2024-07-02-medio-yannick-semedo-reforca-fc-vizela-66842ee7083c9|title=Médio Yannick Semedo reforça FC Vizela|date=2 July 2024|website=Diário do Minho}}</ref>

On 17 July 2025, Semedo signed with [[S.C. Farense|Farense]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=S.C. Farense|url=https://www.scfarense.pt/noticia-detalhe.php?n=394|title=Yannick Semedo é Farense!|trans-title=Yannick Semedo is at Farense!|date=17 July 2025|access-date=24 July 2025|language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
Semedo debuted with the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]] in a 1–0 friendly loss to [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] on 11 June 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/vizela/detalhe/yannick-semedo-de-regresso-a-selecao-de-cabo-verde|title=Yannick Semedo de regresso à seleção de Cabo Verde|website=www.record.pt}}</ref>

